      <section eId="sec_CHC-1285-6">
        <num>CHC 1285.6</num>
        <heading>1285.6.  Hearing</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1285-6__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court shall sign the order setting the time and place for the hearing of the petition for adoption of the Hague Convention adoptee not less than thirty nor more than sixty days after the filing of the adoption petition.  The court may extend this time for good cause, which may include a showing by the department that it has been impossible to gather the necessary data within the time prescribed.  The court may reduce the time to a minimum of fifteen days with written approval of the department and the petitioner.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1285-6__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>At this hearing, the court shall consider:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1285-6__subsec_B__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Any motion to intervene that has been filed.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1285-6__subsec_B__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Any other issues in dispute.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1285-6__subsec_B__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The confidential report of the department.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1285-6__subsec_B__subsec_4">
            <num>(4)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The report of any criminal records or validated complaints of child abuse or neglect concerning the petitioner.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1285-6__subsec_B__subsec_5">
            <num>(5)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The testimony of the parties.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1285-6__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the child to be adopted is twelve years of age or older, the court shall solicit and consider his wishes in the matter.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
